In sci.crypt, U35284@uicvm.uic.edu writes:
>Hello I hope someone here can help me a friend suggested that I post to this
>group. I am interested in getting a general algorithm that outlines VCR plus
>encryption and decryption methods. I have a copy of some PD code accomplishes
>these tasks given the day, month, year, time ect but it is written rather
>cryptically written itself. Therefore, I was hoping that someone might be
>able to point me some source that might contain the more general algorithm.

Check out our paper:

"Decoding a VCR Controller Code" by Ken Shirriff, Curt Welch,
and Andrew Kinsman. Pg 227. CRYPTOLOGIA, Volume XVI Number 3, July 1992.

Published by Rose-Hulman Institute of Technology, Terre Haute IN 47803
812-877-1511

The code you saw was probably written from the information in this
article.

Curt Welch

